
How can decode DO107 device bytes?
1. You must first decode the packet header
2. If the length of the given data (no header length) is greater than the DataLength field (Offset 20 to 24 of bytes) start the parse data part of Device Packet
3. If bit 0 of Falg( offset 8-10 from the bytes) is 1,then MUST uncompress data with lz4 algorithm with block format( not file format)
For example, the following Device Packet:



Header of packet: 
Head=ABAB
TID=E9030000
API version=0001
Flag=0001
MessageType=0100
IMEI=87960B86C70E030
DataLength=0D3080000
CRC=00000000
Bit 0 of Flag is 1 ,So data part of Device Packet MUST uncompress with lz4 algorithm, result of uncompressed data is :



4. After prepare data, according on Message Type value in header part, You Must decode data with relevant message in Message.proto file.For example in top example , MessageType is 0100 that if you decode with littleEndian format , give a  0x0001 value , this value is a MessageType_DataPack_Request in protocol, thus you decode the data with DataPackRequest message.

Google Protobuf provide requirement compiler for C++ ,C# ,Dart,Go , Java and Python language. You can generate the classes you'll need to read and write DataPackRequest messages.To do this, you need to run the protocol buffer compiler protoc on your .proto, for more information see the 
  https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/tutorials link.
